-- Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Centum Investment; Safaricom of Kenya
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-01-06T15:39:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-centum-investment-safaricom-of-kenya.html
Kenya’s  All-Share Index (NSEASI)  advanced for
a second day, rising 0.7 percent to 55.28 in Nairobi, the
highest close since Nov.28.  Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index (SEMDEX)  climbed for a third day,
increasing 0.1 percent to 1,893.93 by the end of trading. The
 Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share Index (NGSEINDX)  rose 0.3 percent to
20,725.3 in Lagos, according to a statement on the bourse’s
website. The  FTSE/Namibia Overall Index (FTN098)  gained less than 0.1
percent to 861.23 in Windhoek.  Centum Investment Co. (CENTUM)  , Kenya’s largest
investment company, gained for a fourth day, advancing 3.6
percent to 14.55 shillings, the highest close since Nov. 21, on
speculation the stock was oversold after the company issued
bonus shares last year. “There is a strong demand because the
market is trying to re-rate it,” George Bodo, an equity
strategist at Nairobi-based Apex Africa Capital Ltd., said by
phone today.  Safaricom Ltd. (SAFCOM)  , east Africa’s biggest mobile-
phone operator, increased for the first time in seven trading
sessions, rising 1.7 percent to 3 shillings as it added new
customers in the three months to September.  To contact the reporter on this story:
